e 6th house cult which has nothing to do with vampires.<br><br>Yes you can contract vampirism from being beaten on by a vampire, but since it's a disease if you get to the point in the main quest that you cure corpus disease then you won't be able to contract it without using console.<br><br>There's no lycanthropy in the main game of morrowind but maybe someone made a mod or something to make it possible. <p><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=105067"><img src="http://sairah.homestead.com/files/ElloneSig.jpg" ALT="Click me baby"></a></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/uphixer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Phixer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/22/02 2:53:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vampirism? (Now Alternative Lifestyles through template)</span><hr size=1> Hold on... it's easy enough to run around and chop on things, and you wanna run around as a wolf in addition to carving things up with a glass sword?  Just for giggles, I took my char, Galtric, to the Red Mountain to take on Dagoth Ur. Wow... Got my ass kicked after he ran to the next room. And nothing else in the game that I've found even came close to killing me. COOL! A Challenge! BRING IT ON!<br><br>You know, polymorph self would be a cool add-on spell for the game... come to think of it.. trying to sneak into that kwama mine and tired of using Calm Creature spells (instead of killing them) all the time? Polymorph self into a kwama worker and go at it. Of course, doing something very un-kwama-like will get you detected but still... just seeing the word from a kwama point of view might be cool for a bit. Maybe understand why those Kwama Foragers seem to have a dagger jammed up their @nus which is why they're so jumpy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/urandomflamer001.showPublicProfile?language=EN>random Flamer 001</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/22/02 3:08:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cableone.net/sarlacc/Animated_Flame.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Vampirism? (Now Alternative Lifestyles through template)</span><hr size=1> If you happen to get vampirism, please refer to my post titled VOS. That should help you get cured, if you want to be cured. It is nice to have the power of the Vampire, but there is a HUGE cost...one of which is you no longer get a good nights rest.<br> <p>random Flamer 001<br>Fluch, kann ich nicht eine verfluchte Sache buchstabieren! <BR>Here Forever! Flame on!</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showPrevMessage?topicID=93.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showNextMessage?topicID=93.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.emailToFriend?topicID=93.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm13.threadCont